@notice Sits behind an upgradeable proxy and routes methods to an appropriate implementation contract. All storage
 will sit inside the upgradeable proxy and this router will authorize the call and re-route the calls to implementing
 contracts.
 This pattern adds an additional hop between the proxy and the ultimate implementation contract, however, it also
 allows for atomic upgrades of the entire system. Individual implementation contracts will be deployed and then a
 new Router with the new hardcoded addresses will then be deployed and upgraded into place.

@dev Delegates the current call to `implementation`.
 This function does not return to its internal call site, it will return directly to the external caller.

getRouterImplementation(bytes4).notice: Returns the implementation contract for the method signature

natspec.notice: Sits behind an upgradeable proxy and routes methods to an appropriate implementation contract. All storage will sit inside the upgradeable proxy and this router will authorize the call and re-route the calls to implementing contracts. This pattern adds an additional hop between the proxy and the ultimate implementation contract, however, it also allows for atomic upgrades of the entire system. Individual implementation contracts will be deployed and then a new Router with the new hardcoded addresses will then be deployed and upgraded into place.
